# Phase 2 Complete: High-Volume Analytics & Executive Dashboard

The underlying sentiment engine has been completely rewritten to scale to tens of thousands of comments, and the user interface has been transformed into a professional analyst's dashboard.

## 1. Relational Database Overhaul
The generic `topic_comments` table approach has been replaced. Your [supabase_schema.sql](file:///s:/FYP/Public%20Sentiment%20Index/supabase_schema.sql) file has been updated with a blindingly fast, two-table relational structure:
- `search_topics`: Stores the topic name and total volume.
- [reddit_comments](file:///s:/FYP/Public%20Sentiment%20Index/app/utils/fetcher.py#24-103): Links directly via `topic_id` with a high-performance **Index**.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Action Required**: You MUST open your Supabase SQL Editor and run the new [supabase_schema.sql](file:///s:/FYP/Public%20Sentiment%20Index/supabase_schema.sql) code to initialize the new tables before the app will work.

## 2. Expanded Data Limits
The extraction engine in [fetcher.py](file:///s:/FYP/Public%20Sentiment%20Index/app/utils/fetcher.py) was doubled in power. It will now fetch up to **250 posts** deep and cleanly extract up to **2000 comments per topic**, guaranteeing massive sample sizes.

## 3. Executive Dashboard UI
The Trends page was completely redesigned:
- **Hero Topic Cards**: The 5 preset topics are now massive graphical cards at the top using your own [.png](file:///s:/FYP/Public%20Sentiment%20Index/app/static/images/theboys.png) images from `app/static/images`.
- **Top Community Voices**: A new custom UI component perfectly mirrors Reddit's interface to highlight the #1 Most Viral Positive Comment and the #1 Most Toxic Negative comment for the loaded topic.
- **Analyst Insights**: The confusing hidden "i" tooltips are gone. Every single one of the 15 charts now features a permanently visible **Analyst Insight** text block right beside the data, explaining in plain English exactly what the chart proves (e.g., "A sudden viral spike in negative posts directly correlates to a controversial event...").

## How to Verify
1. Copy and execute the contents of `supabase_schema.sql` in your Supabase Dashboard.
2. Ensure your Flask server is running.
3. Refresh the Trends page. Notice the new Hero Cards and the empty default state!
4. Run the data seeding script: `python seed_topics.py` to watch it populate the massive new database schema.
5. Click one of the new Dashboard Hero Image Cards to instantly view the Analyst Report.
